secondaryFontFamily.$description: secondary naming was chosen for this variable name based on how many instances of this typeface show up on Bild homepage. This was measured with the Project Wallace analyzer tool.

primaryFontFamily.$description: primary naming was chosen for this variable name based on how many instances of this typeface shows up on Bild homepage. This was measured with the Project Wallace analyzer tool.

tertiaryFontFamily.$description: tertiary naming was chosen for this variable name based on how many instances of this typeface shows up on Bild homepage. This was measured with the Project Wallece analyzer tool.

700BlackFontWeight.$description: 700 is considered black weight because Gotham Condensed is the primary font family (most used in headlines). In other font families 700 is not black weight but bold.

BILD085-50.$description: The 50% opacity on this color makes it equivalent to BILD093.

BILDBlue.$description: This Blue color was taken from the Weather 2024 project.

BILDGreen040.$description: This value of green was found in a text field's text color.

scrim-70.$description: This is used as a background overlay for most high priority alert messages that block the user from proceeding, forcing the user to take an action.

textColorSecondary.$description: This is used on article image source mainly.

surfaceColorTertiaryInverse.$description: This surface color was found on the warning message for logging in with unidentified user or password data.

surfaceColorPrimaryGradient.$description: Used next to sliders buttons and slider container edges for fading out content.

colorSecondaryActive.$description: Use this token for when a component is interacted with and a state change needs to be indicated.

colorPrimaryActive.$description: Use this token for most components that have a hover state. The word active in this design system is used interchangeably with the word hover and pressed. Since hover states do not exist on mobile devices the choice was made to use the word active for representing hover and pressed states.

colorSecondaryActiveInverse.$description: Use this token for when a component is interacted with and a state change needs to be indicated with the use of color.

colorTertiaryActive.$description: Use this token for when a component is interacted with and a state change needs to be indicated.

borderColorMediumContrast.$description: This is the most used color for separators across Bild products.

iconColorInverse.$description: Uses same as separator neutral tone color. Is lighter tone than iconColor in Dark mode.

iconColorConstant.$description: Uses same as separator neutral tone color. Is lighter tone than iconColor in Dark mode.

attentionColorHigh.$description: This color variable is the same as Bild's core brand color. This color has been used in marketing content dedicated to subscriptions and in warning messages found in the subscription process. It can be used in other elements that need to grab the user's attention.

accentColorPrimary.$description: Bild's accent color is the same as its primary color. In some dark mode elements this color changes to white. This is often used on small elements such as accordion arrows that change color when they change state or hover states that use some red on them in light mode.

attentionColorMedium.$description: This color variable is currently used in Bild's horizontally scrolling breaking news headline content. It can be used in other elements that need to grab the user's attention.

attentionColorLow.$description: This color variable is currently used in marketing content dedicated to the BildPur subscription. It can be used in other elements that need to grab the user's attention.

accentColorPrimaryConstant.$description: Use this token when you don't want small accents to change color in dark mode. This is often used on small elements such as accordion arrows that change color when they change state or hover states that use some red on them in light mode.

attentionColorSuccess.$description: Fills and strokes use this for grabbing attention and communicating the sentiment of success.

menuScrolledSurfaceGradient.$description: Used on a thin part at the top of header in navigation menu.

!multitextLinksBorderIdle.$description: !do not use! these variables have been deprecated and multitext link buttons are now classified as partner buttons.

!multitextLinksBorderActive.$description: !do not use! these variables have been deprecated and multitext link buttons are now classified as partner buttons.

!multitextLinksBgIdle.$description: !do not use! these variables have been deprecated and multitext link buttons are now classified as partner buttons.

!multitextLinksBgActive.$description: !do not use! these variables have been deprecated and multitext link buttons are now classified as partner buttons.

!multitextLinksContainerBorder.$description: !do not use! these variables have been deprecated and multitext link buttons are now classified as partner buttons.

labelColorPrimary.$description: This variable references Bild015 in light mode and Bild093 in dark mode.

labelColorPrimaryConstant.$description: Use this when label color needs to remain constant between light & dark mode. This token references Bild015.

labelColorPrimaryInverseConstant.$description: Use this when label color needs to be constant between light and dark mode. This token references the primitive Bild093.

labelColorPrimaryInverse.$description: This variable references Bild015 in light mode and Bild093 in dark mode.

menuItemLabelColorSecondary.$description: The variable can be used on secondary menus that many times show up on dedicated home pages specific to a topic. The menu labels are often times using the color white across color modes.

alertSurfaceColor.$description: On marketing offer surfaces this variable is not used. The alertSurfaceConstant variables should be used.

alertSurfaceColorConstant.$description: On marketing offer surfaces this variable is not used. The alertSurfaceConstant variables should be used.

selectionBorderColor.$description: Checkboxes and Radio buttons use this variable for their border.

heySeparator.$description: This is the most used color for separators across Bild products.

coreColorPrimary.$description: This red color is Bild's main brand color. It remains constant across Light and Dark Mode.

coreColorSecondary.$description: This white color is Bild's secondary brand color. This variable changes across Light and Dark Mode.

coreColorTertiary.$description: This dark grey color is Bild's tertiary brand color. This variable changes across Light and Dark Mode.

coreColorSecondaryConstant.$description: Use this on elements that must maintain the white color even in dark mode.

coreColorTertiaryConstant.$description: Use this on elements that need to maintain the dark color across themes and color modes.

labelTextSurfaceColorPrimaryPrimitiveNam.$description: This variable is only for use in Figma's Design System File. It is automating some of the content in documentation pages.

labelTextColorMode.$description: This is currently for use in this design system's documentation texts. It is a text string made for being used in light and dark mode documentation texts.

ContentGapSpace.$description: These variables were made to experiment with how scaling space could work across different content scaling / size / contrast themes.

StackSpace.$description: These variables were made to experiment with how scaling space could work across different content scaling / size / contrast themes.

LabelFontSize.$description: These variables were made to experiment with how scaling space could work across different content scaling / size / contrast themes.

InlineSpace.$description: These variables were made to experiment with how scaling space could work across different content scaling / size / contrast themes.

articleGalleryATeaserWidth.$description: same as standard teaser width size variable

bildDesignFrameSpace.$description: Variable used in spacing parameters of bild.design webpage mockups. move to bild.design group maybe

menuItemFontSize.$description: This variable is used on the menu link lane and on the mobile side menu drawer.

badgeInnerStackSpace.$description: This space variable is used for creating the top and bottom space between a badge's text label and the surface that the text label is on top of.

badgeInnerInlineSpace.$description: This space variable is used for creating the left and right space between a badge's text label and the badge background surface that the text label is on top of.

standardTeaserWidthSize.$description: variable used for css class stage-teaser standard teaser article width at different device width previews

badgeSubscription&VideoMarginSpace.$description: This variable is used for creating space around the outside of a subscription badge or video icon badge.

badgeStdTeaserSubscription&VideoMarginSp.$description: This variable is used for creating space around the outside of a subscription badge or video icon badge.

largeTitle&ArrowInlineSpace.$description: This variable is used on large title headings that are h2 elements in html and indicate a new section in the user interface. This space changes when a user hovers over the large title.

largeTitle&ArrowInlineSpaceActive.$description: This variable is used for increasing the space between the text and the arrow at the end of the large title text. On mobile devices there is no hover state so this variables values are the same as the default state values.

SeparatorsPremiumAlertFontSize.$description: Values come from comparing NMT Figma File 01_Foundation to online CSS. Online kickers are numbered from 0 to 3.

AvatarBorderRadius.$description: For avatarCorners prioritize the use of percentage value 100% instead of pixel values.

newsTickerTimeLineHeight.$description: Figma currently does not allow for percentages in Line Height variables. The values in this token are the result of multiplying the font size by the line height variable defined on the Bild home css -> newsTickerTime line height: 1.3. Line height for this component does not change across devices.

PagenInlineSpace.$description: This variable is used for making teaser images have zero inline (side) paddings on mobile and Tablet devices.

sectionSpaceMD.$description: desktop matches live site, mobile given more spacing

Kicker1FontSize.$description: Values come from NMT Figma File 01_Foundation; in online CSS this is kicker0

Kicker2FontSize.$description: Values come from comparing NMT Figma File 01_Foundation to online CSS. Online kickers are numbered from 0 to 3.

Kicker3FontSize.$description: Values come from comparing NMT Figma File 01_Foundation to online CSS. Online kickers are numbered from 0 to 3.

Kicker4FontSize.$description: Values come from comparing NMT Figma File 01_Foundation to online CSS. Online kickers are numbered from 0 to 3.

bodyTextLineHeight.$description: Figma's font line height currently does not allow for multipliers as is used on current website css var(--body-line-height)

letterSpacingNegativeXS.$description: This letter spacing was only found in large titles on iOS mobile app large title component.

heyKISpecialNavi.$description: Font style used on Hey AI special navigation sliders.

bodyBookParagraphSpace2x.$description: Use this for article text where paragraph spacings are large.

textLinkBookActive.$description: Use this style for body text links or other text links that are in active state.

standardTeaserHeadline.$description: Standard teasers typography changes more than other teasers. On desktop they have a kicker, a headline and a short text. On mobile devices the short text is eliminated and the headline gains weight at device widths 600px. Then at small mobile sizes the weight drops once again.

standardADTeaserHeadline.$description: Standard teasers typography changes more than other teasers. On desktop they have a kicker, a headline and a short text. On mobile devices the short text is eliminated and the headline gains weight at device widths 600px. Then at small mobile sizes the weight drops once again.

menuItemLabel.$description: Used on menu link lane items and on mobile side menu drawer.

menuItemUtilLabel.$description: Use this tokenized font style for vertically laid out menu items with icons that are more important than the menu link lane items.

SpeciaNaviItemLabel.$description: Used on menu link lane items and on mobile side menu drawer.

labelResponsiveBold.$description: This text style has variables for font family, weight and size. The size variable changes depending on the device mode (handy, tablet, desktop).

label1Bold.$description: Used on mobile site side menu drawer menu items list.

label2BoldUpper.$description: Used on special navi component simiiar to link lane menu items.

largeTitleUppercase.$description: This text style does not have an underline. Across Bild's products this underline fills the horizontal space. This underline should be created on a container that wraps the title.
